I tried the number again, same guy picked up, this time I was more adamant and asked him if he was from a car rental agency, he said yes. I asked if it was Avis, he said no, but they had a tie up with Avis. I told him I was supposed to receive a car at the airport, he said he knew nothing of that, and besides he didn’t have any cars to give anyways. With that he disconnected the phone.     Wanted to share our experience with CochinCarRentals(TourWorldHolidays)

    We rented an Innova car for 8 days as a package Kochi-Munnar-Alleypey-Kochi. Our experience with driver Mr. Prince has been very disappointing. Though it was promised to us that the vehicle and the driver will be available for 8 days, this person would vanish to his home without informing, would claim that he is too tired to drive after driving for only 4/5 hours and would argue when asked to drive slower. Once after dropping us at a beach he vanished on the pretext of having tea and when he came back he alleged that one of his door locks has been broken and started to demand extra money. It was also very disappointing that the agency would never return calls when asked to intervene or at least help locate the driver. Maybe the agency outsources and hence has minimal control over the drivers.

    When I recall the wonderful days we spent in Kerala, the only sour spot was this car rental and we were really relieved to let him go.
